</arg></template>The<space/><bold>Government of the Republic of Belarus</bold><space/>(<template><target>lang-be</target><arg>Урад Рэспублікі Беларусь</arg></template>), which consists of the<space/><bold>Council of Ministers of the Republic of Belarus</bold><space/>(<template><target>Lang-be</target><arg>Савет Міністраў Рэспублікі Беларусь</arg></template>), is the executive branch of state power in<space/><link><target>Belarus</target></link>, and it is appointed by the<space/><link><target>President of Belarus</target></link>. The head of the Government is the<space/><link><target>Prime Minister of Belarus</target></link>, who manages the main agenda of the Government and direct the ministers.</paragraph><heading level='2'>Current cabinet</heading><paragraph>Members of<space/><link><target>Presidium</target></link><extension extension_name='ref'><template><target>cite web</target><arg name="url">http://government.by/en/presidium/</arg><arg name="title">Presidium of the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Belarus</arg></template></extension><space/>are highlighted in yellow.<template><target>outdated</target><arg name="date">December 2014</arg></template></paragraph><table class="wikitable"><tablerow><tablehead>Portfolio</tablehead><tablehead>Name</tablehead></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell>Prime Minister</tablecell><tablecell style="background: #ffffaa;"><link><target>Andrei Kobyakov</target></link></tablecell></tablerow><tablerow><tablecell>First Deputy Prime Minister</tablecell><tablecell style="background: #ffffaa;">Vasily Matyushevsky<extension extension_name='ref' name="ctv"><template><target>cite web</target><arg name="url">http://www.ctv.by/node/502134<space/></arg><arg name="title">Andrei Kobyakov nominated new Belarus' prime minister<space/></arg><arg name="date">27 December 2014<space/></arg><arg name="website"><space/></arg><arg name="publisher">Stolichnoye televidenie<space/></arg><arg name="accessdate"></arg></template></extension></tablecell></ta